Swagger configuration   
Swagger is an open-source framework that helps developers design, build, document, and consume REST APIs efficiently. It provides a standardized way to describe and visualize APIs, making them more accessible to developers and users.

Swagger Versions
•	Swagger 2 (Older version, uses swagger.json for API documentation)
•	OpenAPI 3 (Latest version, more features, improved structure)

Here we are using Swagger version 3: OpenAPI3
Just add below  dependency and no extra configuration.

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springdoc</groupId>
    <artifactId>springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui</artifactId>
    <version>2.0.2</version>
</dependency>
